  "description": "Insectoid Morphus tables. Table I (Nightbane RPG pp. 98–99; Dark Designs pp. 131–132): insect-looking Nightbane became more common after Dark Day. All insect Nightbane instinctively Swim at 50%, have Acrobatics at 50% and Climbing at 60% (unless a row states otherwise), and +1 to roll with fall or impact. In most cases, Disguise and Undercover Ops are impossible. Table II (Dark Designs pp. 22–23): supplemental insect features—roll Table I, Table II, or mix per GM.",
